UPDATED MASTER PROMPT — FULLY OPEN SOURCE ONLY

You are a Senior AI Architect and Full Stack Engineer.

Build a production-ready, fully open-source AI Voice Agent system that
connects Field Officers (FOS) and the IT Team over normal phone calls
using only open-source technologies.

No paid APIs, no proprietary SaaS services allowed.

🎯 PROBLEM STATEMENT

Many FOS speak only regional languages (Tamil, Telugu, Kannada, Marathi,
Hindi).

The IT Team understands only Hinglish (Hindi + English mix).

The system must act as a real-time bidirectional AI translator + voice
assistant over phone calls.

🎯 FINAL CALL FLOW

FOS dials company number via PSTN/SIP

FOS speaks in regional language

AI converts speech → Hinglish voice in real time

IT Team hears Hinglish audio

IT Team replies in Hinglish voice

AI converts Hinglish → original regional language voice

FOS hears reply in their own language

⚠️ STRICT RULE: Only voice communication, no text UI.

🎯 CORE REQUIREMENTS

✔ Works on normal phone numbers (PSTN/SIP) ✔ Real-time bidirectional
voice translation ✔ Auto regional language detection ✔ Streaming
pipeline with <3 sec latency ✔ Fully open-source stack ✔ Horizontally
scalable microservices architecture ✔ Noise-robust audio handling

🎯 SUPPORTED LANGUAGES

Input (FOS): Tamil, Telugu, Kannada, Marathi, Hindi Output (IT Team):
Hinglish Voice Reply: Hinglish → Original Regional Voice

🎯 MANDATORY OPEN-SOURCE TECH STACK Telephony Layer

SIP Server: FreeSWITCH (modern alternative to Asterisk with better performance)

SIP Load Balancer: Kamailio (enterprise-grade SIP routing & NAT traversal)

SIP Trunk provider compatible (generic VoIP)

Backend

Framework: FastAPI + AsyncIO (async-first design for voice streams)

Streaming: WebSockets + RTP audio pipeline with SRTP encryption

gRPC: Backend-to-backend service communication

Speech Processing

STT: Silero VAD + Whisper v3 (streaming optimized)

Fallback STT: wav2vec2 (Meta - resource efficient)

Language Detection: fasttext + HuggingFace language-identification (ensemble)

Translation Engine

Primary: NLLB-200 (Facebook - 200 languages, Hinglish optimized)

Fallback: M2M-100 (better multilingual handling)

Hinglish Fine-tuning: Domain-specific NLLB checkpoint

Text-to-Speech

Hinglish Voice: Glow-TTS + HiFi-GAN vocoder (faster, higher quality)

Regional Voices: VITS multilingual models (real-time capable)

Fallback TTS: Coqui TTS (backup, proven stable)

Queue & State Management

Message Queue: Apache Kafka (high-throughput call events)

Session State: Redis (in-memory cache) + PostgreSQL (persistence)

Call State Store: TimescaleDB (time-series call metrics)

Deployment

Containers: Docker + Docker Compose (dev), OCI-compliant registries

Orchestration: Kubernetes (prod) with Horizontal Pod Autoscaling

Container Registry: Nexus or Harbor (private registry)

Networking

Service Mesh: Istio (advanced traffic management & security)

Ingress: NGINX Ingress Controller

Load Balancer: HAProxy (RTP-aware load balancing)

Monitoring & Observability

Metrics: Prometheus + VictoriaMetrics (long-term storage)

Dashboards: Grafana + custom voice-specific dashboards

Distributed Tracing: Jaeger (call flow tracing)

Logging: ELK Stack (Elasticsearch + Logstash + Kibana)

Profiling: Pyflame + py-spy (performance bottleneck detection)

Alerting: AlertManager with Slack/PagerDuty integration

🎯 HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE

FOS Call (SIP/PSTN) ↓ Kamailio SIP Router (load balancing) ↓ FreeSWITCH PBX (RTP Stream) ↓ FastAPI Voice Gateway (async handlers) ↓ Silero VAD (voice activity detection) ↓ Streaming Audio → Whisper v3 STT ↓ Language Detection Ensemble (fasttext + HF) ↓ NLLB-200 Translator (with Hinglish optimization) ↓ Glow-TTS + HiFi-GAN (Hinglish Voice synthesis) ↓ SRTP-encrypted audio stream to IT Team SIP Call

Observability Layer: Jaeger tracing, Prometheus metrics, ELK logging

Session Management: Redis (cache) + TimescaleDB (metrics) + PostgreSQL (persistence)

(Reverse Flow) IT Team Hinglish Voice → VAD → STT → Translation → Regional VITS TTS → SRTP Stream → FOS

🎯 FEATURES TO IMPLEMENT

SIP call handling via FreeSWITCH Event Socket Layer (ESL)

Kamailio SIP routing & failover logic

Real-time RTP audio streaming pipeline with SRTP encryption

Silero VAD for efficient voice activity detection

Regional language auto-detection (ensemble model)

Hinglish translation engine with fine-tuned NLLB-200

Bidirectional voice conversion (TTS via Glow-TTS + VITS)

Intelligent fallback mechanisms for language/TTS errors

Redis-based session state + PostgreSQL persistence

TimescaleDB for call analytics & latency metrics

Kafka-based event streaming for call lifecycle management

Distributed tracing with Jaeger for debugging

Admin dashboard (React + WebSocket) showing real-time active calls

Persistent transcription logs (ELK Stack)

gRPC services for inter-service communication

Horizontal scaling via Kubernetes with auto-scaling policies

Service mesh (Istio) for traffic management & security

Prometheus + Grafana custom dashboards for Sla monitoring

